class PollutionMonitor {
    private int airQualityIndex;
    private boolean factoryOperational;

    public PollutionMonitor(boolean factoryStatus) {
        factoryOperational = factoryStatus;
        airQualityIndex = factoryOperational ? 150 : 50;
    }

    public void updateFactoryStatus(boolean status) {
        factoryOperational = status;
        airQualityIndex = factoryOperational ? 200 : 40;
    }

    public int getAirQuality() {
        return airQualityIndex;
    }

    public boolean isFactoryOperational() {
        return factoryOperational;
    }
}",

If the observed air quality index decreases significantly, can we infer that the factory has become non-operational without inspecting the factory status directly?
